# https://www.liquidweb.com/kb/how-to-setup-a-python-virtual-environment-on-windows-10/

1. Install python virtual enviroment package
pip install virtualenv


Start a cmd shell in virtual studio 
1. cd to path where you want the virtual environment

2. Create virtual enviroment 
py -m venv project-name # in python project location

3.Activate virtualenv 

cd {location}\env\Scripts\activate.bat {env name} # in cmd shell command

or install gitbash
cd {location}\env\Scripts\
source actiavate {env name}

4. Install virtual env wrapper
pip install VirtualEnvWrapper-win

5. install django
 py -m pip install Django

6. colored terminal output
 py -m pip install colorama

7. proxy settings
..\> set http_proxy=http://username:password@proxyserver:proxyport
...\> set https_proxy=https://username:password@proxyserver:proxyport

8. test it's runnning the
 django-admin --version

9. to deactivate enviroment:

deactivate <envname>